# plt.legend() requires labels to be set first

plt.legend() adds a box showing which line is which. 
It uses the label you set in each plot() call:
Labels must be passed to plt.plot(label="France")

Without labels, legend has nothing to show. 
If you forgot them, you can pass labels directly: `plt.legend(["Spain", "France"])`

Common options:
```python
plt.legend(loc="upper left")       # position
plt.legend(fontsize=12)            # text size
plt.legend(frameon=False)          # remove the box border
```

loc values include "upper right" (default), "upper left", "lower right", "lower left", "center", or "best" (pandas picks the least obstructive spot).


